<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<LinearLayout  xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context=".oil_leak"
    android:background="@drawable/gradient_backgrounf">

    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent"
        android:background="#FFFFFF">

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="match_parent"
            android:orientation="vertical"
            android:background="@drawable/gradient_backgrounf">



            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/head1"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:layout_marginLeft="50dp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="20dp"
                android:text="STEPS TO RESOLVE ENGINE OIL LEAK ISSUE"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2"
                android:paddingTop="20sp"/>

            <com.pierfrancescosoffritti.androidyoutubeplayer.core.player.views.YouTubePlayerView
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="250dp"
            app:videoId="yn2CTZ1MA_Q"
            app:autoPlay="true"
            android:id="@+id/youtube_player_view"
            app:showFullScreenButton="false"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/step1"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@+id/newacc"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:text="STEP 1 Inspect the Intake Gasket "
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2"
                android:textColor="@android:color/holo_red_light"/>

            <ImageView
                android:id="@+id/engine1"
                android:layout_width="302dp"
                android:layout_height="215dp"
                android:layout_marginLeft="25dp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
                android:layout_weight="1"
                app:srcCompat="@drawable/engine1" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/point1"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@+id/newacc"
                android:layout_alignLeft="@+id/engine1"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:text="1. Inside the vehicle, there is a gasket that seals the manifold to the head."
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/point2"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@+id/newacc"
                android:layout_alignLeft="@+id/point1"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
                android:text="2. These parts take the role of distribution the combustion mixture, along with the coolant to the separated intake port. These ports will be placed in the cylinder heads. "
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2"
                />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/Step2"
                android:layout_width="360dp"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:layout_marginBottom="15dp"
                android:text="STEP2  Examine Further To Check The Head Gasket"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2"
                android:textColor="@android:color/holo_red_light" />

            <ImageView
                android:id="@+id/engine2"
                android:layout_width="327dp"
                android:layout_height="231dp"
                android:layout_below="@+id/engine1"
                android:layout_marginLeft="25dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="-6dp"
                android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
                android:layout_weight="1"
                app:srcCompat="@drawable/engine2" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/point4"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@+id/newacc"
                android:layout_alignLeft="@+id/engine1"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:text="1. This is a car part that seals the cylinder head in order to prevent the coolant from getting to the cylinder. "
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/point5"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@+id/newacc"
                android:layout_alignLeft="@+id/engine1"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:text="2. Any leak or damage in this part creates an opportunity for the coolant to enter the chamber."
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/point6"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
                android:text="3.Long story short, it will create white smoke from exhaust pipe. If this part is still fine, we will check the cylinder."
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/step3"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
                android:text="STEP 3 Look For Any Crack In The Cylinder Head"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2"
                android:textColor="@android:color/holo_red_light"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/point7"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:text="1. The cylinder head is the car part that made of aluminum, which is prone to breaking in overheated conditions. "
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/point8"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_centerHorizontal="true"
                android:layout_marginBottom="10dp"
                android:text="2.This part is essential since it connects to the engine block and head gasket. The cylinder head is the car part that made of aluminum, which is prone to breaking in overheated conditions "
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2" />


            <ImageView
                android:id="@+id/engine3"
                android:layout_width="327dp"
                android:layout_height="231dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/engine2"
                android:layout_marginLeft="25dp"
                app:srcCompat="@drawable/engine3" />
            <Button
                android:id="@+id/callmech"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:text="Call Mechanic?"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Body2"
                android:layout_marginLeft="150dp"
                android:layout_marginTop="25dp"
                android:onClick="call_mechanic"
                android:background="@drawable/button_round"
                android:textColor="#ffffff"
                android:elevation="5dp"/>

        </LinearLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</LinearLayout>